 an>What you'll learn:</span>\n\n<span><b>How onboarding can make or break t
 he user experience</b></span>\n<br /><span\n  >Learn how onboarding goes be
 yond a first impression\, and sets users up for success (or failure) with y
 our product.</span\n>\n \n<span><b>How to avoid common (and costly) mistake
 s</b></span>\n<br /><span\n  >Real examples & quick activities to demonstra
 te common mistakes that  can lead to dropoff and a sub-par experience.</spa
 n\n>\n \n<span><b>Actionable tips & tweaks</b></span>\n<br /><span\n  >See 
 how tweaking small design & copy details can lead to big improvements towar
 ds UX and business goals.</span\n>\n 
